                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "As I i can't edit my original message to this thread I want to put in here some context.\n\nCONTEXT:\n\nThe Butlerian Jihad is a Conecpt from Dune: "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Dune:_The_Butlerian_Jihad"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\nIt invokes for me the conecept of a quite drastical discourse with Technology, espedially AI."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "user": "UJFN50C00",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1772368381.485229",
        "edited": {
            "user": "UJFN50C00",
            "ts": "1772369133.000000"
        },
        "client_msg_id": "b67985be-9581-437e-84f0-41fb1bc6b226",
        "text": "In that sense I sent the first 4 Links in which we can see how AI companies try to avoid that their technology gets captured by war interests. But also Postmarket OS design rules in which they try to avoid AI consciously.\n\nSo as people try to define or find a - comfortable - position towards technology. I do find the notion of the Butlerian Jihad interesting. Can we reject AI? Can we reject Parts of AI? What will we do instead? And how do we start talking and thinking about this.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "e35958b94f07",
